  <item>
    <title>Keybindings in Amber's new IDE</title>
    <link>http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/helios-keybindings.html#sec-1</link>
    <author>Nicolas Petton</author>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/helios-keybindings.html#sec-1</guid>
    <pubDate>Mon, 13 Jan 2014 13:10:00 +0100</pubDate>
    <category><![CDATA[helios]]></category>
    <category><![CDATA[amber]]></category>
    <category><![CDATA[smalltalk]]></category>
    <description><![CDATA[
    <div class="pubdate">
    January 13, 2014
    </div>

    <p>
    Amber&rsquo;s new IDE, fondly named Helios, has been built with keyboard
    power users in mind from the beginning. It evolved quite a bit over
    time, and keyboard shortcuts as well as their UI are no exception.
    </p>

    <p>
    Last week we improved the Keybinding helper UI in helios, making it
    more prominent and accessible. The previous version was greatly
    inspired by Emacs&rsquo; minibuffer, and while I&rsquo;m an Emacs user, I think
    this iteration makes it a lot more accessible.
    </p>

    <p>
    Here&rsquo;s a short video demonstrating the new user interface.
